‼️One of the number #1 questions I get during virtual wine tastings! What are the “proper” storage tips for your wine with AND without having a wine fridge‼️

My advice is chill your wine the way YOU want first and foremost but this is a good guide to stick to if you’re not sure what temperature it is you like your wine at…😜

Some tips not mentioned in the reel 👇🏼👇🏼👇🏼

• Bubbles ( all your sparkling) wine should be as cold as it can! If you don’t have a wine fridge your kitchen fridge is around 40-45 degrees which works or throw your bubble on ice to have even more of a chill 🧊🥂

• I enjoy lighter body reds such as Gamay, Grenache, and Pinot Noir pretty chilled personally, especially during the summer. Try popping them in your fridge a couple hours before consuming and see what you think! 

• All wine in general does not like to bounce around in temp so always keep it as stable as possible! 

• Keep all your wine out of direct sunlight or anywhere in the kitchen where there are warm surfaces 👍🏼

• Wine likes to be in a cool dark place, closets will work if you don’t have any fridge storage space 

Want to see more wine storage tips?!

‼️ PINEAPPLE WINE SLUSHIES (extra boozy 😈) 🍍🥥🥂‼️ BOOKMARK ME 👇🏼

Serves ✌🏼

• 2 cups chilled white wine I love using Sauvy B, wine used in this video is @14handswine 

• 1.5 cups frozen pineapple 🍍 

• 1-2 ounce vodka or hard alcohol of your choosing 😈

• Splash of coconut water, you can also add some simple syrup if you need more sweetness! I would add to taste 👅 

• Squeeze of half a lime

• Blend and feel free to add more ice or pineapple for more of a frozen texture! 

Cheers 🥂 

P.S - Thank you @tepawines for the inspo, I need to stock up on more of your wine for next time!!!

In honor of #nationalproseccoweek (last week…🤪🥂) here are some of my new fave Prosecco’s that go sooooo well with a bit of heat from whatever dish your cooking up! 🌶🔥😛🥂 SAVE ME for some Prosecco facts/tips 👇🏼👇🏼‼️‼️ 

• The best Prosecco wines are noted from the hilly sub-region of Valdobbiaden in northwest Italy 🇮🇹 Prosecco is actually the region in Italy, not the grape 🍇 

• Prosecco is made from an Italian grape varietal known as “Glera” 🍇 BUT there can also be a few other indigenous grapes in a Prosecco blend like Bianchetta, Verdiso, and Perera!

• Prosecco is a super food-friendly sparkling wine that goes great with most foods especially seafood, anything fried, and of course, spicy 🌶 

• Prosecco is made in a method called the “tank method” which gives it its like zesty flavors which is different than Champagne 🥂 

Want to learn more about the breakdown of your favorite bubbles like Prosecco?! Book my “all things bubbly” virtual wine tasting and I promise I will make it the most fun and approachable wine tasting you’ve ever done!! 😜🥂👏🏼

‼️ HOT NAPA TIPS PART ✌🏼 from your go-to crazy somm😜

• Be sure you stay at a hotel that has a good breakfast or one that is walking distance somewhere because eating before your big day of wine tasting will save your life! @harvest_inn serves a bomb and pretty affordable breakfast 🥞🥂🥐🍳

• With spooky season coming up, @axrnapavalley is a must visit 😈👻 Yeah the wine is fantastic but the fact that the property is haunted really does it for me… 

• If you want to splurge on one of the more pricey wine experiences, I 💯 recommend @darioushwinery food & wine experience in their private cellar. It’s intimate, delicious, and beyond memorable. You already came to Napa, why not treat yourself? 😉

• If you dine at @oliveandhay make a full evening out of it because there is so much to do at the @meritageresort ! It’s like it’s own little Napa island with live music, wine tastings, and of course the best food! 

• Please don’t forget to hire a private transportation service like I shared in my last reel!!! @northbaywinetours , you won’t regret it ‼️

‼️ NAPA TIPS FROM YOUR GO-TO SOMM 💃🥂👇🏼🍷

• If you’re only visiting wine country for a brief amount of time like me (less than 48 hours) don’t overload your itinerary. Stick to two-three wineries a day at the most for ultimate enjoyment and less rushing / stressing! 

• You MUST pre book a transport service such as @northbaywinetours !!! Uber and Lyft are very difficult to get / rely on especially with spotty service at the wineries. Yes, private transportation services like this can be more pricey but is 💯 worth it. Napa in general is pricey so you might as well book a transport service that will keep your itinerary running smoothly especially if you’re short on time. 👍🏼

• Most hotels in the area offer complimentary tastings at wineries in the area if you provide proof that your a hotel guest. Always speak with the front desk and see which wineries qualify for that! Tastings range anywhere from $30-100 so if you want to get the most bang for your buck be sure to do your research on which hotels offer that. @harvest_inn offers complimentary tastings at wineries such as @whitehalllane , @florasprings @vsattui and more 🥂

• Make reservations for EVERYTHING!!! Now more than ever people are flocking to wine country like crazy and the valley is doing their absolute best to provide their guests with an intimate experience which means no crowds. Most wineries / restaurants offering online booking to make it super easy, book as far out in advance as you can. 👍🏼

• Probably the most important tip of them all. BE KIND AND SHOW PATIENCE with the hospitality industry. We just experienced one of the biggest set backs we could have possibly of had with the pandemic and everyone is doing their best to get back to their “normal” services. 

Stay tuned for part ✌🏼 soon! 🥂
